a/rest/api/2/user?username=he+yongqiang","name":"he yongqiang","key":"he yongqiang","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"He Yongqiang","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"body":"why to add the \"SNAPSHOT\"? I think when we do the release, we will cut a branch. No?\n\nThis made some noise to some local scripts which always use the latest open source trunk, which rely on all the jar files.","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=he+yongqiang","name":"he yongqiang","key":"he yongqiang","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"He Yongqiang","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"created":"2011-01-05T23:23:20.932+0000","updated":"2011-01-05T23:23:20.932+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12494560/comment/12978040","id":"12978040","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=jvs","name":"jvs","key":"jvs","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"John Sichi","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"body":"SNAPSHOT follows the Maven convention for unreleased binaries.  We recently ran into a case where Amazon referred to their binaries as 0.7, even though it hadn't been released yet, so this should help avoid that confusion in the future.\n\nWhen we cut a release branch, we'll remove the SNAPSHOT designation as part of publishing release candidates.\n","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=jvs","name":"jvs","key":"jvs","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"John Sichi","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"created":"2011-01-05T23:36:08.479+0000","updated":"2011-01-05T23:36:08.479+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12494560/comment/12978046","id":"12978046","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=he+yongqiang","name":"he yongqiang","key":"he yongqiang","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"He Yongqiang","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"body":"So it is added to avoid confusion with Amazon's naming...It is still confusing because it still looks like the amazon's 0.7 is a 0.7 release","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=he+yongqiang","name":"he yongqiang","key":"he yongqiang","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"He Yongqiang","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"created":"2011-01-05T23:47:37.786+0000","updated":"2011-01-05T23:47:37.786+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12494560/comment/12978049","id":"12978049","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=jvs","name":"jvs","key":"jvs","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"John Sichi","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"body":"It's added as a best practice to avoid similar confusion in the future.  For the specific case of Amazon, we're in communication with them via email to get them to correct their web pages (specifying SNAPSHOT and the specific revision they based their build on).\n","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=jvs","name":"jvs","key":"jvs","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"John Sichi","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"created":"2011-01-05T23:51:31.489+0000","updated":"2011-01-05T23:51:31.489+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12494560/comment/12978074","id":"12978074","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user